                            <comment id="12677141" author="dkulp" created="Thu, 26 Feb 2009 21:10:47 +0000"  >
&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve added the dynamic import.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, there doesn&apos;t seem to be a way to add an import for com.sun.xml.bind.v2 since we don&apos;t actually use it anywhere at all.  We already have:&lt;br/&gt;
com.sun*;resolution:=optional&lt;br/&gt;
for all the sun stuff and the felix plugin doesn&apos;t find that package since we don&apos;t actually reference it at all.   Thus, the smx bundle will probably need to be used.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12677310" author="sauthieg" created="Fri, 27 Feb 2009 10:47:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the fix&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Concerning the &apos;com.sun.xml.bind.v2&apos; package that was more a general remark: CXF &lt;b&gt;requires&lt;/b&gt; you to use these particular JAXB2 API in an OSGi environment.&lt;br/&gt;
That&apos;s something good to know for users of CXF/OSGi &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
